𝒟𝒾𝒸𝓎 04/14/2023 11:00 PM
Hello cuties, for anyone who may not know me the name is Dicy. I am a 22 year (for a few more days) old finance major from the very mid ass state of kentucky. I in what may come off as a massive shock am a bit of weeb. I am a massive anime fan (see linktree in bio for MAl), who enjoys a wide variety of different things. I am a competitive Pokémon VGC player and judge. when I’m not watching anime or screaming at my rng in Pokémon battles I’m chilling searching for new music or hanging out with friends playing a whole host of games and sports. This is my fourth Org, I made my humble debut in SmORGon season 20 with much of the amazing host team here where I flopped and got 12th. After that I entered Doravivor where I placed 7th and played what I view as my best game out side of threat management. The third game would result in my best placement to date with 4th where I do believe I had a winning game if I won the final challenge but alas we fell short. I’ll attach my Org document below that has a bit more info on my games including their Edgics. I’m beyond excited to play here in such a great community of people and friends. It would be a dream come true if I was able to pull off my first win Here in Snack, but we will see. For anyone who doesn’t know my playing style, I focus largely on the social aspect of the game, I want people to like me and enjoy me being around. This creates many doors for strategic plays. In an ideal world I will sit behind a challenge threat or just a threat player and allow them to be viewed as the leader of the group to hide my true gameplay. Never can be seen as the best threat because that’s a death sentence. I do tend to become a bit game bot like with my strategy but I’m also human who can have emotional outburst that impact my game, hopefully we keep that in check. I have no issues being a villain or hero when it comes to the game. The moves I make aren’t to be like they are to win the game, if people cheer me they cheer me I’m here to play a good entertaining game. Talking Game with Dicy EP 2: Fuck being Humble, I'm a Cocky Bitch Topics: - The numbers in the game - Thoughts on the players - small alliance talk
14:25
The Numbers Walking into the swap we have a good split overall of players from starting tribes with tree from Unagi (Etay, Fones, Stephen), us three from Hokkigai (Aura, Dicy, Slaytan) , and then Mana from the cursed Ebi. This is a favorable swap situation overall, we managed to tie in numbers which keeps us equal in tribe power and avoids the Targeting like occurred on the other tribe with Sake. The three of them walking in together allowed the other four to have a common threat and connect together. This write up is a tad late so ill include the last tribal in this. The numbers currently sit: Unagi - 5 Hokkigai - 4 sake - 2 Ebi - 2 This is actually something important to keep an eye on, We don't want to get to merge (I assume this will be after 2 more votes) where there is a bad split of Original tribes that leads to collective targeting. Best case situation honestly would be for One Unagi and then one Ebi/Sake go with the next vote so that the playing field would be a 4-4-2-1. This would incentivize a Unagi/Hokkigai partnership to keep the last three to play the middle and bounce back and forth. With that situation Merge would be a 8-3, which is pass the majority needed of 6. Now if the numbers don't work out in that fashion things are extremely flexible, we will more then likely walk into merge with the four members of Cuties Please still in the game which is a group of four. We would need two more for the merge vote which I could pull in Rob (If he is there) and then Etay/Fones can pull in the 6th. Another route is that I work with the shattered group that will be walking into Merge. If Sake and Ebi both walk in with there two there is a line were Rob is tight with the Sake two and Treb and I can jump down to them. With Mana this would be a group of six. Now this is the most unlikely outcome on the board to me as Mana hasn't talked a whole lot to me and I have no reason to jump into bed with four people I don't know if I can trust at all when the only link would be Rob. But that's Merge we have a few cycles to see how that will truly shape up. As for the current Swap situation, I am sitting pretty in the numbers. The tribe has seven players, while I sit in an alliance of four for majority. All the while I have some level of a connection to Aura even if I don't fully trust them. Meaning I have connections to four of the six players here that's not myself. I should never be in any danger of going home while here on this tribe. We are setting up the ground work for the social connections needed to have doors open both now and later in the game.
14:26
Thoughts on the Players (if you vanity search, I'm sorry its just game. I love you) Slaytan - He is a person who is more in the inactive then active spector but is a good guy overall. He has a good baseline challenge performance level from what I have managed to witness. Despite him being a good guy and seems easy to talk with he hasn't always been the most interesting person in the world to talk with which is fine, you don't have to be a 10/10 all the time. This however does make me think he social game isn't fantastic but decent. I see Slaytan as a very mid tier player. Someone I can trust for now but know I will never lose to unless my threat level spikes and its a collective measure. Outside of that I can play the social game in circles around them and be in the better situation between the two of us. Etay - Etay is my fucking boy man. I swear if I went with my heart just a little bit more Etay would of been number one in my trust rankings. I do think I'm Etays number one ally in this game which is a good thing to have in my pocket. Etay's challenge abilities from a very limited sample size seems decent to good. His social game I believe is a mixed bag overall. I do think that its solid overall, but there are types of people I think Etays vibe will push away, which gives me an area to play my own social game in that I believe can connect to anyone. Etay however is the player in this game I have met so far I think could match my social capital in the game. Which has its own Pros and Cons with it. It allows me to always have another player to point to as a social threat, however if he gets eyes on him for his social play, I probably pick up looks as well. I need to be careful with how I play out this game with Etay however, I have a track record of having a blindside to some people and I can see Etay falling into my blindside. However I think Etay is a very good person to have around and work with, I do believe I can out play him in the end game once it comes down to it. Fones - I have vibed well with Fones so far in the game, very likable guy that feels very similar to myself. Based on everything I have heard and seen from him so far Fones may be the Smartest person I've met so far in the game. However, he's a busy busy boy. Which leaves the social game sector wide open to be abused. Fones Challenge performance also was talked up well by Etay. I believe Fones to be my biggest competitor in so far. His supposed Challenge ability and clear intellect is scary, however much like Slaytan I know I can play circles around his social game currently which how his schedule is. The real threat would be if he gains more free time because I get the vibe his social game is very solid as well. All of that being said, he is the prefect shield for me to hide behind in this game and to use. He can always be throw under the bus for being a much bigger game threat then myself. Aura - I Honestly don't have a whole lot to say about Aura in the game. They aren't bad at anything but I also see no part of their game that is outstanding.
